DynamicGraphImpl

public DynamicGraphImpl(Graph graph)
Constructs a new DynamicGraph that wraps a given Graph. The time interval is [-infinity, +infinity].

Parameters:
graph - wrapped Graph

Parameters:
graph - wrapped Graph

high - the right endpoint of the interval
Throws:
NullPointerException - if graph is null.
IllegalArgumentException - if low > high.

Note that it doesn't matter what estimators you give for 'static' attributes.

getSnapshotGraph

public Graph getSnapshotGraph(double point)
Description copied from interface: DynamicGraph
Returns a "snapshot graph", i.e. a graph for the given point of time. The default estimator is used (Estimator.FIRST). It means that the first time intervals of nodes/edges are checked for overlapping with the point.

Specified by:
getSnapshotGraph in interface DynamicGraph
Parameters:
point - the given point of time
Returns:
a "snapshot graph", i.e. a graph for the given point of time.

getStrongSnapshotGraph

public Graph getStrongSnapshotGraph(double point)
Description copied from interface: DynamicGraph
Returns a "strong snapshot graph", i.e. a graph for the given point of time. "Strong" means that if EVERY time interval of considered node/edge overlaps with the point it is considered as a part of snapshot.

Specified by:
getStrongSnapshotGraph in interface DynamicGraph
Parameters:
point - the given point of time
Returns:
a "snapshot graph", i.e. a graph for the given point of time.
